title: Sticky Clarence
description: Everything Clarence comes into contact with sticks to his body - a pen, a can of beans, even one of his chickens! Eventually, Clarence becomes the center of a big ball of objects.

title: Lonely Lonnie
description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo record themselves telling scary stories in the treehouse.

title: Pizza Hero
description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

title: Clarencio Magnifico
description: Clarence performs a magic act for some of Aberdale's senior citizens.

title: Motel
description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

title: Brains TV
description: After a marathon of classic sitcom episodes, Clarence becomes stuck as alter-ego "Clarry," an obnoxiously overacting sitcom version of himself. It's up to his friends and family to help him snap out of it, or face life with a new Clarence.

title: Anywhere but Sumo
description: When Clarence realizes Sumo has made a new group of friends at his new school, he becomes jealous and confused. Will Clarence accept a school life void of Sumo, or scheme his way into making their friendship work?

title: RC Car
description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

title: Cloris
description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

title: Hit the Piñata  Music Video
description: Sing along to this pinata song written by Simon Panrucker.

title: Separation Anxiety
description: After talking, passing notes and throwing pencils at the ceiling in class, Ms. Baker separates Clarence and Sumo. They devise ways to communicate to each other from across the room in a series of gags.

title: Birding with Guyler
description: Guyler spends a day bird watching in Bendle Park - and makes a new special friend.

title: Big Boy
description: In order to get them to notice he's more mature, Clarence draws chest hairs on himself and decides to show them off!

title: Claw Machine
description: At the Pizza Swamp arcade, Clarence convinces passerby Vu to use his skills to free Clarence from the claw machine.

title: Etiquette Clarence
description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

title: Sumo Goes West
description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

title: Doodle Battle
description: Clarence and his pals find a large piece of paper and have fun doodling on it.

title: Belson Touch
description: After learning about King Midas' gold touch during a lesson about Greek Mythology, Clarence daydreams about having a Belson touch that turns anything he touches into Belson.

title: Percy in Have a Ball
description: Naive Percy invites his strangely quiet classmate Gilben over to play, and to show Gilben his prized ball collection.

title: Merry Moochmas
description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

title: Valentimes
description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

title: Bucky and the Howl
description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

title: Belson's Backpack
description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

title: Rainy Day
description: Clarence and his friends play in the rain and enjoy their cozy evenings with family.

title: Capture the Flag
description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

title: Clarence for President
description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

title: Video Store
description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo visit their local video store to rent a movie, but discover it's all rented out! Each of them have a different idea of what tape to bring home, and must enlist the help of a tie breaker to figure it out.

title: Beans
description: Clarence attempts to wake a sleeping dog.

title: Beauford T. Pusser
description: Inspired by the short Every Child, an oprhan ktten is passed from kid to kid until it finally makes its way to Ms. Baker, who names him Beauford T. Pusser.
